## Conjecture (CPRR)
- Hypothesis: research artifacts from background agents are
  expensive to regenerate (1117 lines of bytes-on-the-wire MCP
  research is non-trivial to redo) and should land in source
  control as soon as the agent finishes, even if the consuming
  code work hasn't started yet. Untracked research is a fragile
  state.
- Hypothesis: a second agent picking up against FreeBSD will
  benefit from having both documents on main rather than
  regenerating context from scratch.

